                    <span>This book is gives an excellent synthesis as to how freedom was experienced in various regions of the South after 1863.  One of the finest books within the historiography of American slavery and freedom.  Litwack goes to great lengths explaining the freedom experience, the failures of the Freedmen's Bureau and the hesitations ex-slaves felt after 1863.  A must read and must have for anyone interested in slavery, its aftermath and Reconstruction.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Beautifully Written with detailed descriptions of AfAm Strug</div>
